00:16:38,297 --> 00:16:40,788
[ Alarm Clock Ringing ]

242
00:16:47,439 --> 00:16:50,738
Time to get to work.
The sun'll be up soon.

243
00:16:50,809 --> 00:16:54,939
- [ TV.'Man Speaking Spanish ]
- Let's go!

244
00:16:57,716 --> 00:16:59,707
Your granddad and I
started out together...

245
00:16:59,785 --> 00:17:02,777
wildcattin' oil wells
down in Louisiana.

246
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:04,880
Made some money.
We each bought cattle spreads...

247
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:07,892
as a hedge against
the oil runnin' out.

248
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,087
Of course,
he really made it.

249
00:17:10,162 --> 00:17:13,063
- Nice to own your own little piece ofTexas, right?
- Yight.

250
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:43,027
Just from there-

251
00:17:43,095 --> 00:17:45,529
eight feet
from the center.

252
00:17:45,597 --> 00:17:47,588
What?

253
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:50,464
Lunch will be sent
'round about 11:00.

254
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,930
Well, how far
am I supposed to go?

255
00:17:56,008 --> 00:17:57,942
[ Chuckles ]
Don't worry.

256
00:17:58,010 --> 00:18:00,342
You'll run out of posts
before you run out ofTexas.

257
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:05,074
I wish I had a dollar
for every fence post I've ever set.

258
00:18:06,552 --> 00:18:08,486
Matter of fact, I do.

259
00:18:08,554 --> 00:18:11,955
- [ Mock Chuckle ]
- [ Door Opens, Closes ]

260
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:29,140
[ Speaking Spanish ]

261
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:16,219
Hey.

262
00:19:19,591 --> 00:19:22,458
What do you think?

263
00:19:23,529 --> 00:19:26,123
[ Truck Door Opens, Closes ]

264
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:31,969
No! Hey!

265
00:19:32,037 --> 00:19:36,736
Aw! Come on, man!

266
00:19:36,942 --> 00:19:39,433
[ Girlfriend On Cell Phone ]
So, I'm dying to know. What did you get?

267
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:42,605
Uh, it's complicated,
but it involves land...

268
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:45,377
building materials
and slave labor.

269
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:47,418
They're giving you
a shopping mall?

270
00:19:47,486 --> 00:19:50,148
[ Laughing ]
Not exactly.

271
00:19:50,222 --> 00:19:53,282
So it must be the land, right?
They're giving that to you?

272
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:57,590
- Uh, land's got a lot to do with it, yeah.
- You don't sound too sure.

273
00:19:57,663 --> 00:20:01,929
Well, whatever it is, I gotta survive
this geriatric cowboy...

274
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:06,061
until he gives it to me
or when I get back or-

275
00:20:08,574 --> 00:20:10,508
or when I'm finished.

276
00:20:10,576 --> 00:20:12,510
Finish what?

277
00:20:12,578 --> 00:20:14,978
You know what?
Let me get back to you, okay?

278
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:17,481
 Jason, what are you-

279
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:21,082
[ Exhales ]
So that's it.

280
00:20:39,037 --> 00:20:41,130
[ Sighs ]

281
00:21:23,181 --> 00:21:25,411
[ Grunts ]

282
00:21:40,098 --> 00:21:42,032
Yeah.

283
00:21:53,478 --> 00:21:55,207
[ Exhales ]

284
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,426
Let's go.

285
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:11,485
I'm not done.

286
00:22:12,731 --> 00:22:14,722
Work's never done
on a ranch.

287
00:22:20,572 --> 00:22:22,733
[ Men Speaking
Spanish ]

288
00:22:31,149 --> 00:22:33,140
All right. Whatever.

289
00:22:54,339 --> 00:22:56,307
[ Airplane Departing ]

290
00:23:02,013 --> 00:23:05,744
You know, you do any work
like you just did...

291
00:23:05,817 --> 00:23:08,377
you can do anything.

292
00:23:19,431 --> 00:23:22,059
Now, aren't you
forgettin' something?

293
00:23:22,134 --> 00:23:25,934
- I don't think so. Shoot.
- The gift.

294
00:23:26,004 --> 00:23:28,837
I came here to pick up a gift.
Yemember?

295
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:32,775
[ Laughing ]

296
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:37,671
That was the gift?

297
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:40,013
I do manual labor
for a month...

298
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:43,851
and you're trying to tell me
it was a favor- to me.

299
00:23:43,922 --> 00:23:46,288
- The gift of work.
- Wow.

300
00:23:46,358 --> 00:23:48,690
- Congratulations.
- Look, Hamilton.

301
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:51,786
Just tell me what
my total inheritance is. I'm over this.

302
00:23:54,299 --> 00:23:56,824
Where are you going?
Where is he going?

303
00:23:56,902 --> 00:23:58,893
Can you tell him
to come back, please?

304
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:01,962
Mr. Hamilton.
Mr. Hamilton.

305
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:04,531
- [ Door Closes ]
- Hey.

306
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:06,668
Mr. Hamilton, sir.
Please.

307
00:24:09,014 --> 00:24:12,745
I think it's only fair I know the amount
of money we're dealing with here. Don't you?

308
00:24:12,818 --> 00:24:14,752
I've been gone for a month.

309
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:18,017
Just tell me-
What do I have to do? What is it?

310
00:24:18,089 --> 00:24:21,058
Red said,
''a series of gifts.''

311
00:24:21,126 --> 00:24:23,560
But let me add
a personal note.

312
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:26,495
I, too, think
this is a waste of time.

313
00:24:26,565 --> 00:24:30,262
But it will end shortly,
because you are going to fail.

314
00:24:30,335 --> 00:24:33,463
I expect you to fail
and to fail miserably.

315
00:24:33,538 --> 00:24:35,563
Now, if you do want
to continue...

316
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:37,904
make an appointment
with Miss Hastings.

317
00:24:40,345 --> 00:24:43,781
Okay. Look. Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Mr. Hamilton.

318
00:24:43,849 --> 00:24:46,283
[ Sighs ]

319
00:24:46,351 --> 00:24:50,151
I've been acting like a moron
about this whole thing, and I'm sorry.

320
00:24:50,222 --> 00:24:53,680
And now I- I see exactly
what you and Red have in store for me...

321
00:24:53,758 --> 00:24:55,783
and I think
it's exceedingly beneficial.

322
00:24:57,596 --> 00:24:59,587
So, what's the next gift?

323
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:03,267
You'll know.

324
00:25:06,638 --> 00:25:09,766
[ Engine Rewing ]

325
00:25:21,052 --> 00:25:22,986
Howdy.

326
00:25:25,390 --> 00:25:27,381
[ Door Closes ]

327
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:40,471
Wait. Wait.

328
00:25:40,539 --> 00:25:43,235
That's an $8,000
paint job!

329
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:45,333
[ Shouts ]

330
00:25:45,410 --> 00:25:47,344
[ Chuckling ]

331
00:25:47,412 --> 00:25:49,972
You don't begin to live
until you've lost everything.

332
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:52,516
Heck, I've lost everything
three or four times.

333
00:25:52,584 --> 00:25:55,178
It's the perfect place
to start.

334
00:25:55,253 --> 00:25:57,517
Now, for most
of your adult life...

335
00:25:57,589 --> 00:25:59,921
you have been
the life of the party...

336
00:25:59,991 --> 00:26:03,392
and an easy touch
for a lot of weak hangers-on.

337
00:26:03,461 --> 00:26:06,157
Now let's see who
your real friends are.

338
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:08,563
[ Device Beeps ]

339
00:26:08,633 --> 00:26:12,262
I was at your funeral, and there wasn't
a single person there...

340
00:26:12,337 --> 00:26:16,637
who wasn't on your payroll or didn't
have something to gain from your death.

341
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:19,370
What exactly is he
asking me to do?

342
00:26:19,444 --> 00:26:22,743
He wants you to come back
at the end of the month...

343
00:26:22,814 --> 00:26:24,941
with one true friend.

344
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:34,957
[ Laughing ]
Thank you.

345
00:26:36,995 --> 00:26:40,897
- And how were the lobster tails?
- It was fine, thanks.

346
00:26:40,966 --> 00:26:43,025
The lady was enjoying
the Montrachet.

347
00:26:48,139 --> 00:26:50,369
And sir, the Margaux.

348
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:52,342
I hope it met
your expectations.

349
00:26:52,410 --> 00:26:54,571
It was terrific.
Thank you.

350
00:26:54,646 --> 00:26:59,310
We don't get too many requests
for the '7 8.

351
00:26:59,384 --> 00:27:02,182
It's a bit too pricey
for some of our patrons.

352
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,449
I'll just leave this
with you then.

353
00:27:10,895 --> 00:27:12,624
[ Sighs ]

354
00:27:12,697 --> 00:27:16,258
Caitlin, where do you
see our relationship?

355
00:27:17,602 --> 00:27:21,595
- What are you asking me, Jason Stevens?
-Just thinking.

356
00:27:21,673 --> 00:27:24,471
How long have we
been going out?

357
00:27:24,542 --> 00:27:27,306
Uh, an appropriate
amount of time.

358
00:27:27,379 --> 00:27:29,677
- Long enough.
- See? My thoughts exactly.

359
00:27:29,748 --> 00:27:34,378
I was thinking that maybe
it's time to take us... more seriously.

360
00:27:34,452 --> 00:27:36,215
Yes?

361
00:27:36,287 --> 00:27:39,188
But there's something
I want to ask you first.

362
00:27:39,257 --> 00:27:43,091
 Jason, if you're talking about a prenup,
isn't that sort of passé?

363
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:45,857
Well, see, I'm in-
I was thinking-

364
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:48,262
[ Clears Throat ]
Excuse me, sir.

365
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:50,824
The charge card company
declined the charge.

366
00:27:50,902 --> 00:27:54,633
That's impossible. I don't have a credit limit.
Just run it through again.

367
00:27:54,706 --> 00:27:58,164
It's always our practice
to run it through again...

368
00:27:58,243 --> 00:28:00,234
but they declined.

369
00:28:02,981 --> 00:28:04,915
Okay.

370
00:28:04,983 --> 00:28:08,043
So, I was thinking, um...

371
00:28:08,119 --> 00:28:12,283
well, maybe, it'd be a good time
for me to move in with you.

372
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:16,225
Uh, you move in with me?
Why? Half my wardrobe's at your penthouse.

373
00:28:16,294 --> 00:28:20,128
Just for a change of scenery.
Besides, I'm remodeling my place.

374
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:23,827
A remodel? But-Who's your designer?
I know everyone in town.

375
00:28:23,902 --> 00:28:26,803
I should've said
I'm beginning to remodel.

376
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:29,601
I've only really started
with the demolition.

377
00:28:31,142 --> 00:28:34,543
I'm sorry, sir.
Your bank is on the line.

378
00:28:34,612 --> 00:28:36,637
They'd really like
to speak with you. I must insist.

379
00:28:36,715 --> 00:28:38,808
Look, guys. I'm having
a little bit of a setback.

380
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:41,010
It's nothing that can't be fixed.
All right?

381
00:28:42,721 --> 00:28:44,916
[ Sighs ]

382
00:28:44,989 --> 00:28:49,449
- [ No Audible Dialogue ]
- Sweetie, I'm switching accounts right now...

383
00:28:49,527 --> 00:28:52,587
and I'm...
temporarily out of money.

384
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:55,030
Is there a way
you could pay for this?

385
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:01,539
[ Breath Quavers ]

386
00:29:01,606 --> 00:29:04,268
 Jason, you're, um-

387
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:07,901
You're, uh...

388
00:29:10,215 --> 00:29:12,809
asking me
to pay the bill?

389
00:29:12,884 --> 00:29:15,717
- It's-
- [ Sniffles ]

390
00:29:21,793 --> 00:29:23,852
[ Sighs ]

391
00:29:25,997 --> 00:29:28,625
[ Sputtering ]
What?

392
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,032
Yo, dude,
I'm rollin' over.

393
00:29:31,102 --> 00:29:33,036
What do you mean
I can't?

394
00:29:33,104 --> 00:29:36,540
I have been there for you
countless times.

395
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,838
You owe me. That's it.
Bottom line.

396
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:41,174
Who was the one who loaned you
10 grand last year?

397
00:29:41,246 --> 00:29:43,806
I could come up with a better excuse
when I was 12 years old.

398
00:29:43,882 --> 00:29:46,908
All I need is a place to sleep.
I don't get what the problem is.

399
00:29:46,985 --> 00:29:49,681
You can let me spend the night.
One night. Hello?

400
00:29:49,754 --> 00:29:52,245
[ Man: Yecorded Message ]
Sorry. Your service has been disconnected.

401
00:29:52,323 --> 00:29:55,724
- Can I help you? Yeah, shut up.
- No. Nothing, thanks.

402
00:30:05,436 --> 00:30:07,370
[ Gasps ]
 Jason.

403
00:30:07,438 --> 00:30:09,565
Um- Uh,
what a surprise.

404
00:30:09,641 --> 00:30:12,701
- Mom, you're never gonna believe this.
- I'm afraid I can't let you in.

405
00:30:14,145 --> 00:30:16,511
I'm having a bit of a situation.
I need some help.

406
00:30:16,581 --> 00:30:20,517
- I need to borrow some money.
- Of course you do. Everyone needs money.

407
00:30:20,585 --> 00:30:22,815
[ Clears Throat ]
Uh- [ Sighs ]

408
00:30:22,887 --> 00:30:26,254
Didn't your grandfather
leave you anything?

409
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:28,588
What are you talking about?
He hated me.

410
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:30,628
 Jason, he did not.

411
00:30:30,695 --> 00:30:35,064
He didn't come around much, but, uh,
I always thought it was because of me.

412
00:30:35,133 --> 00:30:37,260
It doesn't matter.
Do you have any extra spending cash?

413
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:40,463
I would love
to help you.

414
00:30:40,538 --> 00:30:42,904
- But I can't.
- You can't?

415
00:30:42,974 --> 00:30:46,000
They told me specifically that you would be
comin' around for money...

416
00:30:46,077 --> 00:30:48,068
and that I was not
to give you anything.

417
00:30:48,146 --> 00:30:51,115
But I'm your son, Mom.
That's what you're supposed to do.

418
00:30:51,182 --> 00:30:53,844
If I violate
their instructions...

419
00:30:53,918 --> 00:30:57,285
I am out everything-
everything.

420
00:30:57,355 --> 00:31:00,051
So for the sake
of the greater good...

421
00:31:00,124 --> 00:31:02,558
I must insist
that you leave.

422
00:31:02,627 --> 00:31:04,618
I'm not gonna upset
the whole applecart...

423
00:31:04,696 --> 00:31:06,926
just because you're facing
a few challenges.

424
00:31:06,998 --> 00:31:10,900
I'm sorry. I just
cannot help you.

425
00:31:10,969 --> 00:31:13,233
- Thanks.
- [ Sighs ]

426
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:32,147
- [ Yelping ]
- Ow!

427
00:31:34,859 --> 00:31:37,259
[ Can Clattering ]

428
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:54,710
Hey, man. You're-
You're on my bench.

429
00:31:57,949 --> 00:31:59,940
You're on my bench.

430
00:32:01,352 --> 00:32:03,286
Beat it.

431
00:32:03,354 --> 00:32:07,222
- A simple ''no''would have sufficed.
- Fine. No.

432
00:32:07,292 --> 00:32:11,023
- No, what?
- No, you cannot sit on this bench.

433
00:32:11,095 --> 00:32:13,256
This is not your bench.
This is a city bench.

434
00:32:13,331 --> 00:32:16,391
- Go sit on another bench.
- But it's my bench.

435
00:32:16,467 --> 00:32:18,765
I've gotjust as much
right to it as anybody.

436
00:32:18,836 --> 00:32:21,304
- It's a free country, you know.
- [ Laughs ]

437
00:32:21,372 --> 00:32:23,306
See, that's where
you're wrong.

438
00:32:23,374 --> 00:32:25,672
Name one thing
in this country that's for free.

439
00:32:25,743 --> 00:32:28,678
You need money for everything.
Without money, you're nothing.

440
00:32:28,746 --> 00:32:31,180
Look at you.
No money. No food.

441
00:32:31,249 --> 00:32:33,217
No family. No friends.
Nothing.

442
00:32:33,284 --> 00:32:36,151
Besides, I'm sitting
on this bench now.

443
00:32:36,220 --> 00:32:38,381
This is my bench.
Okay?

444
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:44,694
I'll flip you for it.

445
00:32:44,762 --> 00:32:46,730
Fine.

446
00:32:53,838 --> 00:32:56,398
- [ Murmurs ]
- [ Sighs ]

447
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:59,568
I have a quarter.

448
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:02,970
Thanks.

449
00:33:08,419 --> 00:33:11,820
[ Scoffs ]
Oh.

450
00:33:11,889 --> 00:33:14,858
Well, aren't you gonna
chase him for it?

451
00:33:14,926 --> 00:33:17,417
Beat it, kid.

452
00:33:17,495 --> 00:33:20,362
I've been watching you.
You're not a real bum.

453
00:33:20,431 --> 00:33:23,958
We saw you at a funeral.
Quite the entrance.

454
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:28,798
- What were you doing at-
- My mother and I come here for lunch every day.

455
00:33:28,873 --> 00:33:31,637
Except, right now,
she doesn't know where I am.

456
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:34,940
- [ Woman In Distance ] Emily.
- [ Sighs ] Whatever.

457
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:38,449
Emily.
Oh. Emily.

458
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:42,077
- You must really be having a bad life.
- Come on. Right now.

459
00:33:42,153 --> 00:33:45,247
I was just having a pleasant conversation
with this gentleman.

460
00:33:45,323 --> 00:33:49,589
- Leave us alone, please.
- Dear, don't be ridiculous.
Sorry to disturb you. Come on.

461
00:33:49,660 --> 00:33:51,821
That's okay. I'm not the one
who's disturbed.

462
00:33:51,896 --> 00:33:53,864
Some friend you are.

463
00:33:53,931 --> 00:33:55,865
Thanks a lot, poser.

464
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:58,060
You know what I've said
about talking to strangers.

465
00:33:58,136 --> 00:34:01,469
- He's not a real bum.
- Hey. Whoa, whoa. Wait, wait, wait.

466
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:04,372
Okay, this is gonna sound
really, really strange...

467
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:06,842
but I'm just gonna
come out and say it.

468
00:34:06,911 --> 00:34:09,675
I'll make a deal with you.
I need a friend.

469
00:34:09,747 --> 00:34:12,341
But only for a little while,
and, uh...

470
00:34:12,417 --> 00:34:17,354
in return, I don't know,
I'll take you both to Disney World.

471
00:34:17,422 --> 00:34:20,323
- Excuse me?
- [ Sighs ]

472
00:34:20,391 --> 00:34:23,792
- I need a friend.
- Explain yourself.

473
00:34:23,861 --> 00:34:27,661
- It's complicated.
- No, it's not.

474
00:34:27,732 --> 00:34:30,098
It's pathetic.

475
00:34:30,168 --> 00:34:32,830
- Come on. Now, just because-
- Mom, I told you.

476
00:34:32,904 --> 00:34:36,203
- He's not a real bum.
- Okay.

477
00:34:36,274 --> 00:34:38,708
Oh, dude, come on.

478
00:34:43,714 --> 00:34:46,046
[ Growling, Barking ]

479
00:34:46,117 --> 00:34:49,177
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

480
00:34:53,724 --> 00:34:55,658
[ Chatter On Walkie-Talkie ]

481
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:01,899
She doesn't even like
